WEBVTT

00:00.300 --> 00:03.934
Quorum — the Nonprofit Board OS.

00:04.234 --> 00:14.684
Two quick connections make the Calendar shine: Google Calendar, and Zoom. Let's set up
both — it takes about a minute, and you only do it once.

00:14.984 --> 00:28.050
Open Calendar. If yours isn't connected yet, you'll see this friendly screen instead of
a grid. Click Connect Google Calendar, sign in with your Google account, and allow
access.

00:28.350 --> 00:37.216
And there it is — the month view, alive. From now on, board events sync with the
calendar you already check every day.

00:37.516 --> 00:48.542
Now Zoom. Up by the month name, click Connect Zoom... and done. From here on, meetings
and motions can schedule their own video calls.

00:48.842 --> 00:57.420
See the Join Zoom buttons that just appeared down the rail? That's the payoff — one
click into any board call, forever.

00:57.720 --> 01:08.914
If you ever need to switch accounts, Disconnect is right there too. That's the plumbing,
done. Next: keeping your thoughts together, with Notes.
